TITLE/EDITION Advanced Practice Nursing, Fifth Edition: Core Concepts for Professional Role Development
By: Kathryn A. Blair PhD FNP FAANP (Author), Michaelene P. Jansen PhD RN-C GNP-BC NP-C (Author)
Paperback: 350 pages
Publisher: Springer Publishing Company; 5 edition (April 10, 2015)
Language: English
ISBN-10: 0826172512
ISBN-13: 978-0826172518
NOTE: This is the standalone ebook and may not include access codes that come packaged with the bound book




The Fifth Edition of this topflight text on Advanced Practice Registered Nurse role development is completely updated and expanded to encompass the full sphere of current practice roles. These include interprofessional, global health, and leadership roles and such practice issues as credentialing, prescriptive authority, and liabilities. The book encompasses the diverse expertise of contributors from a wide variety of practice settings and reflects the competencies identified by key stakeholder organizations such as ANA, NONPF, NACNS, AANA, ACNM, and AACN. With a focus on everyday realities of APRN practice in a rapidly changing health environment, it delivers essential information on the multifaceted role of APRNs as they transition into practice and professional arenas
